function clean_column(col::String)
    return replace(strip(lowercase(col)), "-" => "_")
end
```

This function takes a `String` as input and returns a `String` with the specified modifications. It first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip()`, then lowercases the string using `lower()`, and finally replaces any hyphens (`-`) with underscores (`_`) using `replace()`.
